[
  {
    "text": "Betsy Langowski: In 2017, the iPhone X was released.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=2"
  },
  {
    "text": "Linking against the iOS 11 SDK ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=5"
  },
  {
    "text": "let your app take advantage of the beautiful new display.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=7"
  },
  {
    "text": "This year, we are introducing the iPhone XS, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=12"
  },
  {
    "text": "the iPhone XS Max, and the iPhone XR.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=15"
  },
  {
    "text": "While iPhone XS has been ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "completely redesigned from the ground up, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=20"
  },
  {
    "text": "the screen size is the same as an iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=22"
  },
  {
    "text": "so this video will focus on the iPhone XS Max and iPhone XR ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "with their all-new resolutions.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=30"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app primarily uses UIKit frameworks ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you've already adapted your app for iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "you should be in great shape.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=37"
  },
  {
    "text": "All you'll need to do is link against iOS 12 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=39"
  },
  {
    "text": "to take full advantage of these great new phones.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you need a refresher on how to update your app for iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=45"
  },
  {
    "text": "and now iPhone XS Max and iPhone XR, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "check out the video, \"Building Apps for iPhone X.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=53"
  },
  {
    "text": "This video walks you through making sure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "the TrueDepth camera doesn't occlude your UI, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=58"
  },
  {
    "text": "ensuring your UI elements are positioned ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "away from the Home indicator, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=63"
  },
  {
    "text": "and other common adjustments that you may need to make.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "While most of the heavy lifting is done for you by UIKit, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=68"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may still need to optimize your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "and this video provides guidance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=73"
  },
  {
    "text": "that is great for iPhone XS Max and iPhone XR, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as iPhone X.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's talk about a couple of things ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "that we've made better for you this year ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=82"
  },
  {
    "text": "to make updating your apps for iPhone XS Max ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=84"
  },
  {
    "text": "and iPhone XR a breeze.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=86"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you watched \"Building Apps for iPhone X,\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=89"
  },
  {
    "text": "you remember the importance of testing in landscape mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=92"
  },
  {
    "text": "One of the places this is critical is in collection views.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=95"
  },
  {
    "text": "I've built this really simple sample app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=99"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is just a collection view controller, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=101"
  },
  {
    "text": "embedded in a navigation controller, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is embedded in a tab bar controller.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=106"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are offsets to space out the cells, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=108"
  },
  {
    "text": "but otherwise this is just using the defaults.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "At first glance, in portrait, it looks really good.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "But in landscape, this app has a problem: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=115"
  },
  {
    "text": "the cells on the left side are behind the TrueDepth camera.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=118"
  },
  {
    "text": "In order to address this, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "the collection view's section inset reference ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=122"
  },
  {
    "text": "needs to be set to the safe area, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=125"
  },
  {
    "text": "instead of the default content inset.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "This can be done in code, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "and when the iPhone X was first released, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=130"
  },
  {
    "text": "that was the only way to do it.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=132"
  },
  {
    "text": "But since this app was built with storyboards, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "in more recent Xcode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "we can make this change directly in Interface Builder.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=137"
  },
  {
    "text": "With the collection view selected in the storyboard, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "we can select the Size Inspector ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=143"
  },
  {
    "text": "and change the Inset From value to safe area.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=145"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now when I build and run my app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=149"
  },
  {
    "text": "my collection view avoids the TrueDepth camera in landscape, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=151"
  },
  {
    "text": "no code changes needed.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "Auto layout is the Cocoa and Cocoa Touch layout system.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=157"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app uses auto layout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "you'll find that most of the work of optimizing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=162"
  },
  {
    "text": "for new screen sizes, like those on the iPhone XS Max ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "and iPhone XR, is done for you.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you aren't taking advantage of the great benefits ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "you get from auto layout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=172"
  },
  {
    "text": "now is definitely the time to update, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=174"
  },
  {
    "text": "because this year we dramatically improved ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=176"
  },
  {
    "text": "its performance.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=178"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here are some examples ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=180"
  },
  {
    "text": "of iOS 11's auto layout performance in gray ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=182"
  },
  {
    "text": "compared with iOS 12's auto layout performance in blue.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=185"
  },
  {
    "text": "Look how much less time moving trees take in iOS 12 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=189"
  },
  {
    "text": "compared with iOS 11.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=192"
  },
  {
    "text": "Using auto layout in your app just got a lot faster.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=194"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you'd like a behind-the-scenes look ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "at how we did it, check out the WWDC 2018 video, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"High Performance Auto Layout.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=203"
  },
  {
    "text": "One change for iPhone XS Max and iPhone XR specifically ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=206"
  },
  {
    "text": "is in the behavior of UISplitViewController ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=210"
  },
  {
    "text": "in landscape.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=213"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's a lot like how it works in Mail in portrait mode on iPad.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=214"
  },
  {
    "text": "Take a look at this very simple test app I made ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=218"
  },
  {
    "text": "running in the iPhone XS Max simulator.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=220"
  },
  {
    "text": "My master view with four cells ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=224"
  },
  {
    "text": "comes in with the press of a button ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=225"
  },
  {
    "text": "and is dismissed similarly.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=227"
  },
  {
    "text": "My app got this behavior automatically ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the new hardware ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=231"
  },
  {
    "text": "because I set a displayModeButtonItem.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=232"
  },
  {
    "text": "This behavior will also be set if you use presentsWithGesture.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=235"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a peek at what this looks like in code.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=239"
  },
  {
    "text": "In my App Delegate, I've gotten ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=241"
  },
  {
    "text": "the UISplitViewController's displayModeButtonItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=243"
  },
  {
    "text": "and set it as the left bar button item ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=246"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the navigation bar for my customer to tap.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=249"
  },
  {
    "text": "So now I'm opted-in to the behavior ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=252"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the iPhone XS Max and iPhone XR.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm also setting presentsWithGesture to true.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=257"
  },
  {
    "text": "This makes it possible for my customer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=261"
  },
  {
    "text": "to access the master view with a swipe.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is optional, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=265"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it can be set to false if needed for your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=266"
  },
  {
    "text": "One thing to note.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=268"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you've relied on setting ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=269"
  },
  {
    "text": "preferredDisplayMode to automatic, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=271"
  },
  {
    "text": "this is now the automatic behavior.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=273"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you've done some customization ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=275"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you'd like to opt out of this behavior, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=277"
  },
  {
    "text": "simply avoid using the displayModeButtonItem entirely ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=279"
  },
  {
    "text": "and set presentsWithGesture to false.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=283"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can also set preferredDisplayMode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "to allVisible.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=287"
  },
  {
    "text": "OK.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's move on to talk about some common pitfalls.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=290"
  },
  {
    "text": "Some apps may have a background image set ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=294"
  },
  {
    "text": "to specific dimensions, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=295"
  },
  {
    "text": "or certain assets pinned to a spot on the screen.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=297"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is most common in games, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=300"
  },
  {
    "text": "but your app may use a technique like this ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=302"
  },
  {
    "text": "for a variety of reasons.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=304"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app has set a scaled image, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=305"
  },
  {
    "text": "when you run it on an iPhone XS Max or iPhone XR, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=308"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may notice your content is scaled incorrectly.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=311"
  },
  {
    "text": "Unlike apps that use standard UIKit frameworks, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=314"
  },
  {
    "text": "while these phones are still new, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=317"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may need to do a little bit of special-casing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=318"
  },
  {
    "text": "and tell your app -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=321"
  },
  {
    "text": "or the framework your app is using -- ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "about the new screen.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=324"
  },
  {
    "text": "The display dimensions for both ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=326"
  },
  {
    "text": "the iPhone XR and iPhone XS Max ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "are 414 points wide by 896 points tall.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=330"
  },
  {
    "text": "As you're building your assets, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=335"
  },
  {
    "text": "keep in mind that the iPhone XR is a 2x device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=337"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the iPhone XS Max is a 3x device.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "So in pixels, the resolution of iPhone XR ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=344"
  },
  {
    "text": "is 828 by 1,792 pixels.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=347"
  },
  {
    "text": "The resolution of the iPhone XS Max ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=352"
  },
  {
    "text": "is 1,242 by 2,688 pixels.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=355"
  },
  {
    "text": "Caution! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=361"
  },
  {
    "text": "You should only hard-code screen dimensions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=362"
  },
  {
    "text": "if your framework absolutely requires it.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=364"
  },
  {
    "text": "While this can make your game or similar app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=367"
  },
  {
    "text": "work right out of the gate, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=369"
  },
  {
    "text": "you should avoid using these methods ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=371"
  },
  {
    "text": "unless you absolutely need to.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=372"
  },
  {
    "text": "Please let UIKit do the work for you ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=374"
  },
  {
    "text": "and use auto layout instead.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=377"
  },
  {
    "text": "While it may be tempting to force your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=379"
  },
  {
    "text": "to behave in specific ways on various hardware models, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=381"
  },
  {
    "text": "you should avoid making special cases ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=384"
  },
  {
    "text": "per piece of hardware.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=386"
  },
  {
    "text": "This will take time away from developing new features, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=388"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it's largely redundant work.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "Additionally, when your code is running ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=393"
  },
  {
    "text": "on a model of phone it doesn't recognize, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=394"
  },
  {
    "text": "unexpected problems can occur.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=397"
  },
  {
    "text": "This can hurt your customers ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=399"
  },
  {
    "text": "if you aren't able to update your app right away.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=400"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you made a special case for your iOS app to run on iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=403"
  },
  {
    "text": "now you have to redo all your hard work ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=406"
  },
  {
    "text": "for iPhone XS Max and iPhone XR.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=408"
  },
  {
    "text": "Even if you need to set dimensions within your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=412"
  },
  {
    "text": "to accommodate graphical needs, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=414"
  },
  {
    "text": "do not search for a device model ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=415"
  },
  {
    "text": "and gate behavior behind that string check.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=417"
  },
  {
    "text": "You should never write code that reads like, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=420"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Is this an iPhone X? Do A.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=422"
  },
  {
    "text": "Else? Do B.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=424"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is a great opportunity to make sure ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=426"
  },
  {
    "text": "you have adopted safe-area insets ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "universally throughout your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=430"
  },
  {
    "text": "and save your future self a lot of time and effort.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now is also a great time to be really diligent about ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=435"
  },
  {
    "text": "how you're branching your code ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=438"
  },
  {
    "text": "when you're looking for feature availability.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=439"
  },
  {
    "text": "Just like the other iPhones you already support, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=442"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as iPhone SE and all iPads, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=444"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPhone XR doesn't support 3D Touch and dual cameras, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=447"
  },
  {
    "text": "so it's important that you don't rely on those behaviors.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=451"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's use 3D Touch as an example.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=454"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Home app is a fantastic example of an application ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=456"
  },
  {
    "text": "that uses 3D Touch on supported devices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=459"
  },
  {
    "text": "but provides the full feature set ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=462"
  },
  {
    "text": "on devices that do not support 3D Touch, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=463"
  },
  {
    "text": "or for users who may have turned it off.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=465"
  },
  {
    "text": "Checking whether a device uses 3D Touch is simple.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=469"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a look at some sample code.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=472"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, check at launch whether or not ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=475"
  },
  {
    "text": "the device supports the feature, as shown highlighted here.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=478"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, remember a user can turn off 3D Touch ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=481"
  },
  {
    "text": "while your app is running.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=484"
  },
  {
    "text": "Therefore, you should also do this check ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=486"
  },
  {
    "text": "as part of your implementation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=488"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the traitCollectionDidChange delegate method.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=490"
  },
  {
    "text": "In either case, branch your code to use an alternative ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=493"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as UILongPressGestureRecognizer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=496"
  },
  {
    "text": "for devices that don't support 3D Touch, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=499"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that the full feature set is represented for all devices.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=501"
  },
  {
    "text": "When in doubt, make sure your code can handle nil ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=505"
  },
  {
    "text": "and is robust enough to gracefully fail ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=507"
  },
  {
    "text": "when getting back something unexpected.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=509"
  },
  {
    "text": "For most apps, there won't be much work ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=513"
  },
  {
    "text": "for you this year to support iPhone XS, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=515"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPhone XS Max, and iPhone XR, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=517"
  },
  {
    "text": "especially if you already are optimized for iPhone X.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=520"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you need any support, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=524"
  },
  {
    "text": "there's lots available from the iPhone X videos ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=525"
  },
  {
    "text": "and this year's WWDC 2018 sessions.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=528"
  },
  {
    "text": "Check out the related content, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=532"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you can find more\non developer.apple.com.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-207/?time=534"
  }
]